    <h2>ğŸ§© Background</h2>
    <p>
      Todayâ€™s dataset â€” <strong>total_health_spending_per_person_us.csv</strong> â€” provides country-level statistics on how much is spent on health care per person (in USD) over time.  
      This data offers an opportunity to explore how **health expenditure** relates to **health outcomes**, **economic capacity**, and **global equity**.
    </p>
    <p>
      With this dataset, you can ask questions like:  
      ğŸ’¡ Does higher per-person health spending translate into better health outcomes or longer life expectancy?  
      ğŸ’¡ How do spending patterns differ across income groups, regions, or time periods?  
      ğŸ’¡ What are the outliers â€” countries that spend less or more for comparable outcomes?
    </p>
